  "text": "Authors used Arksey and O'Malley's scoping framework with Levac, Colquhoun and O'Brien's 2010 revisions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This six-stage framework includes: (i) identifying the research question; (ii) identifying relevant studies; (iii) selecting studies; (iv) charting data; (v) collating, summarizing, and reporting results and (vi) stakeholder consultation [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
